# Run sheets are a compiled artifact with strict JSON frontmatter, and the shipped
# worked example is tracked. Pin them to LF so the file in the working tree matches
# the file in the repo on every platform.
#
# This is defence in depth, not the fix: the parsers in render-runsheet.mjs and
# verify-runsheets.mjs accept \r?\n, so a user's own CRLF run sheet still loads.
# Without both, a Windows checkout (core.autocrlf defaults on) rewrites the example
# to CRLF and an LF-only anchor reports "No JSON frontmatter" on a valid file —
# invisible in CI, which runs on Linux and checks out LF.
*.run.md text eol=lf
